  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  
  <h3>Is cryptocurrency legal in Kenya?</h3>
  <p>Yes, cryptocurrency is legal in Kenya, but it's not recognized as legal tender. The Central Bank of Kenya has warned about the risks but hasn't banned it.</p>
  
  <h3>How do I avoid crypto scams in Kenya?</h3>
  <p>‚Ä¢ Avoid "guaranteed returns" schemes
  ‚Ä¢ Don't share private keys or recovery phrases
  ‚Ä¢ Use reputable exchanges
  ‚Ä¢ Be cautious of celebrity endorsements
  ‚Ä¢ Research before investing</p>
  
  <h3>Can I buy Bitcoin with M-PESA?</h3>
  <p>Yes, you can buy Bitcoin with M-PESA through P2P platforms like Binance P2P, Paxful, or LocalBitcoins. Some exchanges also support direct M-PESA deposits.</p>
  
  <h3>What's the minimum amount I can invest in crypto?</h3>
  <p>You can start with as little as KES 100 on most platforms. Some exchanges have minimum purchases as low as KES 50.</p>
  
